
[1]bask

   B'ASK, v.i. [The origin of this word is not obvious.]

   To lie in warmth; to be exposed to genial heat; to be at ease and
   thriving under benign influences; as, to bask in the blaze of day; to
   bask in the sunshine of royal favor. The word includes the idea of some
   continuance of exposure.

   B'ASK, v.t. To warm by continued exposure to heat; to warm with genial
   heat.
